# Marketplace catalog filters

- `useMarketplaceListings` must load the **full catalog once** via `useCatalog()` and apply `filterCatalogServices()` + pagination in memory.
- Do **not** key React Query on filter params or call `fetchCatalogPage()` per filter change — that causes ~3s Supabase round-trips on every checkbox.
- Reserve `fetchCatalogPage` for integration tests or future server-side pagination when the catalog is too large for client filtering.
- Show loading only on the initial catalog fetch (`isLoading && !data`), not when filters change.
- `sortBy: "popular"` must use `sortCatalogByPopularMix()` — stage popularity scores tie across products (all Assess = 100), so a flat sort shows only one type on early pages.
- Featured carousel (all categories): `FEATURED_SERVICE_VARIANT_IDS` in `src/data/featuredServices.ts` with `popularityRank` / `popularity_score` 110; DBA script `workspace/dba-catalog-copy/update-featured-services.sql`.
- `fetchCatalogFromSupabase` loads `marketplace_listings_view` then joins variant extras (including `product_content.description` per variant). Never use product-level `short_description` alone for card copy.
- `enrichCatalogListExtras` runs in the background for tags/features/remix/descriptions when placeholder data is shown first.
- `useCatalog` must use `placeholderData: getCatalogPlaceholder` so the grid renders immediately (fixture or sessionStorage cache).
- `CatalogPrefetch` in App warms the catalog on first load.
- `useBestSellers` must derive from `useCatalog()` — never trigger a second full catalog fetch.
- Do not block the marketplace UI with a “Loading catalog” empty state when placeholder data exists.
